<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Reset Password</title>
</head>

<body>
<div class="form-container">
    <h2>Reset Password</h2>
    <form action="/password" method="post">

        <div class="form-info">
            <label for="email">Email:</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="Click Here">
        </div>


        <div class="form-info">
            <label for="newPassword">New Password:</label>
            <input type="password" id="newPassword" name="newPassword" placeholder="Click Here">
        </div>

        <div class="form-info">
            <label for="newPasswordCheck">Re-Enter New Password:</label>
            <input type="password" id="newPasswordCheck" name="newPasswordCheck" placeholder="Click Here">
        </div>

        <button id="btn-pw">Submit New Password</button>
        <p id="pw-reset-message"></p>
    </form>
</div>

<!--
Some things you can style using CSS:
- .form-container  (Main container for the form)
- .form-info       (input fields that take in text)
- #btn-pw      (Submit button for the signup form)
- #pw-reset-message  (Message displayed before redirecting after reset)
-->